<subSubSection id="C371F9D3FFC0FFDFFE86FEA9FE3AFECC" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD4AA58FFC0FFDFFE86FEA9FE3AFECC" blockId="13.[264,1323,283,550]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFE86FEA9FE14FEA7" bold="true" box="[312,445,283,309]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BD1DBFFC0FFDFFDEAFEAEFD6DFEA7" box="[596,708,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhoori">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFDEAFEAEFD6DFEA7" box="[596,708,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">sindhoori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the brownish red colour of the insect in Malayalam.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C371F9D3FFC0FFDFFE86FED9FCE5FDB4" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD4AA58FFC0FFDFFE86FED9FCE5FDB4" blockId="13.[264,1323,283,550]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFE86FED9FE03FE17" bold="true" box="[312,426,363,389]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BD1DBFFC0FFDFFE02FEDEFD0BFE17" box="[444,674,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhoori">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFE02FEDEFD0BFE17" box="[444,674,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Phaelota sindhoori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is remarkable among the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BD1DBFFC0FFDFFBD7FEDEFB7AFE17" box="[1129,1235,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFBD7FEDEFB7AFE17" box="[1129,1235,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Phaelota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to lack of suprafrontal sulcus (weak suprafrontal sulcus is present in other species). Receptacle of spermatheca is longer than the duct while duct is nearly two times as long as the receptacle in the other two Indian species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BD1DBFFC0FFDFFCA9FE56FC0EFE6F" box="[791,935,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhoori">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFCA9FE56FC0EFE6F" box="[791,935,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. sindhoori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BD1DBFFC0FFDFFB33FE56FA8DFE6F" box="[1165,1316,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaishakha">
<emphasis id="B91F764AFFC0FFDFFB33FE56FA8DFE6F" box="[1165,1316,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. vaishakha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated as discussed under the latter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
